PrecisOrder rescinding the National Transportation Agency Order No. 1991-R-170, which ordered the Canadian National Railway Company to abandon, effective April 3, 1993, the operation of a segment of the Montmagny Subdivision over which VIA Rail Canada Inc. precis:
Order rescinding the National Transportation Agency Order No. 1991-R-170,
which ordered the Canadian National Railway Company to abandon, effective
April 3, 1993, the operation of a segment of the Montmagny Subdivision
over which VIA Rail Canada Inc. Montréal-Campbellton-Halifax and
Montréal-Gaspé passenger services operate, necessary to prevent
disruption of VIA'S service to Lévis and Québec City.
